extends layout

block content
  
  section.flex.space-x-4.pr-3
    article.place-items-start.w-34.h-34.grid.grid-cols-1.py-2.pl-3
      each worker in workers
        article.max-w-sm.p-6.bg-white.border.border-gray-200.p-6.rounded-lg.shadow(class='dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700')
          a
            h5.mb-2.text-2xl.font-bold.tracking-tight.text-gray-900(class='dark:text-white')  #{worker.username}
          p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
            |Bloodtype: #{worker.bloodtype}
          p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
            |Status: #{worker.status}
          a.inline-flex.items-center.px-3.py-2.text-sm.font-medium.text-center.text-white.bg-blue-700.rounded-lg(href='#', class='hover:bg-blue-800 focus:ring-4 focus:outline-none focus:ring-blue-300 dark:bg-blue-600 dark:hover:bg-blue-700 dark:focus:ring-blue-800')
            | Read more

        br
        

    // Aqui empieza la barra de instrucciones
    article.ml-1.py-2.pl-3
      article.max-w-screen-xl.p-6.bg-white.p-6.border.border-gray-200.place-items-start.w-34.h-34.rounded-lg.shadow(class='dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-700')
        a(href='#')
          h5.mb-2.text-2xl.font-bold.tracking-tight.text-gray-900(class='dark:text-white') Instructions for Wearing the Oximeter Device
        p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
          | 01. Prepare the Device: Ensure that the oximeter device is fully charged. The device consists of a wristband containing an ESP-32 microcontroller and a MAX30102 oximeter sensor.
        p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
          | 02. Secure the Wristband: Place the wristband around your wrist, with the sensor facing the inner side of your wrist.
        p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
          | 03. Adjust the Fit: Adjust the strap for a snug but comfortable fit. Make sure the device sits securely on your wrist without causing discomfort or hindering movement.
        p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
          | 04. Position the Sensor: Align the sensor area of the device with the pulse point on your inner wrist, where your radial artery is located.
        p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
          | 05.Secure the Strap: Fasten the wristband securely to prevent it from moving around during your activities. It should not be too tight to restrict circulation.

        p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
          | 06. Monitoring: Once activated, the oximeter will start monitoring your heart rate and blood oxygen levels. Keep your wrist steady and avoid excessive movement for accurate readings.
        p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
          | 07. Notifications: The device will show the data on supervisor's computer
        p.mb-3.font-normal.text-gray-700(class='dark:text-gray-400')
          | 08.Removing the Device: When you're done using the device, simply unstrap it from your wrist. If the device is not waterproof, avoid exposing it to water or moisture.